[normal]The HA also appears to have no concept whatsoever of cost-effectiveness. 
[normal]The design standar
[normal]ds f
[normal]or
[normal] trunk roads such as the A14 have over the past decade 
[normal]become more and more stringent and grandiose, 
[normal]meaning
[normal] t
[normal]hat schemes conceived for example a decade ago, become hugely more expensive, or indeed unaffordable, when reworked “to modern standards”. What the country needs are many new or updated roads, implemented in a much more modest and cost-effective way, so al
[normal]lowing many more schemes to be actually implemented, and hence greatly improving the collective ‘return on investment’ for the government (or indeed other funding sources).
[normal]An example of this was the implementation of the long and desperately needed 
